<br>
The uniforms are not gone, but they are different.  They're no longer wearing the gray vests.  But they are wearing the long sleeve white shirts and ties (the striped ties with their school colors).  The only bad part is that they are not wearing their robes as often and in the books, wizards and witches wear their robes as their main article of clothing.<br>
<br>
Now if you've read the book, you will be very pleased to know that Snape does in fact get turned into wearing a dress.  They showed it in the preview.  Very funny!  I can't wait to see that part in the movie.<br>
<br>
They didn't show the full appearance of a dementor.  What they did show was the train compartment door sliding open and a tattered black garment swaying in the wind, and then a bony hand reaching around the door.<br>
<br>
They've taken some artistic licensing.  We will see Aunt Marge blow up like a balloon, but she's outside.  In the preview, we see her flying up into the sky with relatives below standing outside on the grass.  In the book, they were in the kitchen.<br>
<br>
Crookshanks is in the movie and looks very much as described in the book.<br>
<br>
Overall, the first preview makes the movie look like the book - the absolute best in the series!  I'm so excited, I can't wait for it to come out! <p>**********************************************<br>
